main event: A couple observed a bright light in the sky while driving from Dexter to Roswell, New Mexico on November 22, 1966.
interesting points: The light hovered, then shot straight up, and was observed as a blinking white light.
The object was described as a 'pulsating light' that moved at high speeds, made sharp turns, and appeared to disappear and reappear.
The object followed the couple's car all the way to Roswell, then moved off to the south.
The object was estimated to be around 20 degrees in size.
The sighting lasted for about an hour.
sighted object: a bright, pulsating light in the sky
location: 20 miles south of Roswell, New Mexico
witnesses: a couple driving from Dexter to Roswell
